<section class="content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-num">§ 01 · The charge</div>
    <h2 class="serif">Milestone 04, in <em>three phases.</em></h2>
    <p class="section-deck">Build the architecture. Articulate the strategy. Show what's possible. Prepare the floor for what comes next.</p>

    <p class="lede">SAE arrived at Milestone 04 with two milestones of upstream work already complete and a third running in parallel. Internal Discovery (M01) had surfaced the institutional condition: powerful programs, fragmented journey, invisible brand, a turning point under new leadership. Audience Discovery (M02) had quantified the opportunity: 15% awareness against 80–94% appeal, four addressable segments, four personas. Program Innovation (M03) was producing the structural skeleton of a portfolio (the V4 grid). Milestone 04's job was to give all of that a coherent strategic and visual frame.</p>

    <p>The Statement of Work, executed in August 2025, scoped the engagement around three connected phases:</p>

    <div class="three-col">
      <div class="col-feature">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--gold);">Phase 01</div>
        <h4>Brand <em>architecture.</em></h4>
        <p>The structural system. How the parent, the sub-brand, the program families, and the individual programs relate. Designed to make new programs easy to add and existing equity easy to preserve.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-feature">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--gold);">Phase 02</div>
        <h4>Brand <em>strategy.</em></h4>
        <p>The Brand Map applied at the Workforce Development sub-brand level. Stakeholders, positioning, promise, narrative — the spine that gives every program a shared center to ladder to.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-feature">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--gold);">Phase 03</div>
        <h4>Future-state <em>explorations.</em></h4>
        <p>The visual demonstration. Three design objectives, two design anchors (one new program, one existing). A controlled-flexibility system that keeps the parent visible while letting programs breathe.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sidebar">
      <div class="sidebar-label">What Milestone 04 is — and what it is not</div>
      <h4><em>Foundation</em>, not finish.</h4>
      <p><strong>What it is.</strong> A strategic and structural foundation — research-led, audience-grounded, design-aware — that prepares the ground for the next phase of SAE Workforce Development.</p>
      <p><strong>What it is not.</strong> Not a rebrand of SAE. Not a final brand system. Not a launched program identity. The core SAE parent brand remains intact and untouched in this engagement.</p>
      <p><strong>What comes next.</strong> Implementation — taxonomy, governance, the parent-level Brand Map pass, and the migration of existing programs into the new architecture. The hub names these in §05.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

