<section class="content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-num">§ 06 · What's next</div>
    <h2 class="serif">From foundation, to <em>implementation.</em></h2>
    <p class="section-deck">Five recommended next moves. Each is sized to be commissioned independently. Each unlocks downstream value disproportionate to its cost.</p>

    <p class="lede">The work documented across these three phases is foundational. Implementation is the work that follows. The five moves below are the operational consequences of what M04 produced — investible, sequence-able, and tractable in the next eighteen months.</p>

    <ul style="margin-top: 32px;">
      <li><strong style="color: var(--ink);">01 · Commission the brand taxonomy.</strong> Translate the architecture into operational naming and identity standards that staff and partners can apply daily. The single highest-leverage next deliverable.</li>
      <li><strong style="color: var(--ink);">02 · Stand up the brand governance function.</strong> Identify the small group accountable for architecture integrity. Define their authority. Begin operating immediately, even before the taxonomy is finalized.</li>
      <li><strong style="color: var(--ink);">03 · Commission the parent-level Brand Strategy.</strong> Apply the Brand Map at the SAE International level. Articulate the Purpose-through-Narrative spine that every future sub-brand pass will inherit.</li>
      <li><strong style="color: var(--ink);">04 · Decide on the high-school path.</strong> Make the institutional choice — acquire, partner, or build — for closing the high-school program gap. The choice has implications for capital, capacity, and timeline; making it is more important than which option wins.</li>
      <li><strong style="color: var(--ink);">05 · Reclassify the connective infrastructure.</strong> Move the digital hub, LMS, CRM, and e-commerce platform investments into capital infrastructure planning. Treat them as foundational technology, not departmental discretionary spend.</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin-top: 32px;">Each is in scope for either continued partnership with Merit or for in-house execution by the SAE team. The full reasoning, options, and trade-offs for each are documented in the long-form report.</p>
  </div>
</section>

